A man believed to be in his 20s, was hit by a train and died near
Gold Street in Springs, on Wednesday morning. ER24 spokesperson Russel Meiring when paramedics arrived on the
scene, they found the relevant authorities in attendance. “Upon closer inspection, paramedics found the body of a man lying
beneath the train,” Meiring said. According to Meiring paramedics assessed the man and found that he
was already dead. “Nothing could be done for him and he was declared dead,” Meairing
said. The details surrounding this incident are not yet known. Meiring said local authorities were on the scene for further
investigations.